name: Theory and Practice: Three- Dimensional Work
description: An exploration of ideas and practice with an emphasis on three-dimensional work.
prerequisites: 2.5 credits at the B- or C-level in VPS courses including 0.5 credit taken from: VPSB59H3, VPSB71H3, VPSB77H3, VPSB86H3, or VPSB88H3; students enrolled in the Specialist and Major programs in Studio Art must also complete ACMB01H3 and VPHA46H3
